{"id": "EUVD-2023-60164", "enisaUuid": "b8c70799-59da-3e17-84e1-adccc10b83e4", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmd/raid10: fix null-ptr-deref in raid10_sync_request\n\ninit_resync() inits mempool and sets conf->have_replacemnt at the beginning\nof sync, close_sync() frees the mempool when sync is completed.\n\nAfter [1] recovery might be skipped and init_resync() is called but\nclose_sync() is not. null-ptr-deref occurs with r10bio->dev[i].repl_bio.\n\nThe following is one way to reproduce the issue.\n\n  1) create a array, wait for resync to complete, mddev->recovery_cp is set\n     to MaxSector.\n  2) recovery is woken and it is skipped. conf->have_replacement is set to\n     0 in init_resync(). close_sync() not called.\n  3) some io errors and rdev A is set to WantReplacement.\n  4) a new device is added and set to A's replacement.\n  5) recovery is woken, A have replacement, but conf->have_replacemnt is\n     0. r10bio->dev[i].repl_bio will not be alloced and null-ptr-deref\n     occurs.\n\nFix it by not calling init_resync() if recovery skipped.\n\n[1] commit 7e83ccbecd60 (\"md/raid10: Allow skipping recovery when clean arrays are assembled\")", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T18:30:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T18:30:33", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/38d33593260536840b49fd1dcac9aedfd14a9d42", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/14964127be77884003976a392c9faa9ebaabbbe1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bdbf104b1c91fbf38f82c522ebf75429f094292a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/68695084077e3de9d3e94e09238ace2b6f246446", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b50fd1c3d9d0175aa29ff2706ef36cc178bc356a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/99b503e4edc5938885d839cf0e7571963f75d800", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9e9efc77efd1956cc244af975240f2513d78a371", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a405c6f0229526160aa3f177f65e20c86fce84c5", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53832"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53832"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "08c5311c-1605-3f3e-9bad-8375a5971538", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3.10"}, {"id": "44a31861-e8ab-3218-9a74-a505a62ddcff", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7e83ccbecd608b971f340e951c9e84cd0343002f <99b503e4edc5938885d839cf0e7571963f75d800"}, {"id": "5f14b03e-433a-30d3-bb0a-99566741437f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7e83ccbecd608b971f340e951c9e84cd0343002f <38d33593260536840b49fd1dcac9aedfd14a9d42"}, {"id": "78f5466b-22b9-3bd0-a15f-7fb77006e6fc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7e83ccbecd608b971f340e951c9e84cd0343002f <b50fd1c3d9d0175aa29ff2706ef36cc178bc356a"}, {"id": "7bc4e6af-307e-3456-ad71-a7dae3c2856f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7e83ccbecd608b971f340e951c9e84cd0343002f <14964127be77884003976a392c9faa9ebaabbbe1"}, {"id": "7c281bf6-f95d-3db1-9af5-866ef714a5f8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.19.283"}, {"id": "7ce488d1-6ec7-378b-a546-515200e7516b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.111"}, {"id": "856c84be-6513-3157-8eb8-ebb389ddba6a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.28"}, {"id": "8f9d49cd-cfaa-313d-b1ca-1cf01b549dd0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.180"}, {"id": "9d2f7c8b-8f01-3f8d-95dc-34bdd960fa11", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.15"}, {"id": "b0576860-fcb0-36d2-bf5b-1912524ffd63", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "b1a12c8a-2d00-3e97-8ddd-38591c18bcaa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.4"}, {"id": "b8c74686-cb07-3a9c-8750-0a3e2383de88", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7e83ccbecd608b971f340e951c9e84cd0343002f <a405c6f0229526160aa3f177f65e20c86fce84c5"}, {"id": "bd6d702b-0df6-3f59-8de5-e42dc452f5fd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7e83ccbe